<br>
In LDoN, there are three kinds of chest traps... magic, cursed, and mechanical.  Mechanical can be handled by a rogue or bard, cursed by a priest, and magic by an int caster, using spells gotten from LDoN.  Note that traps can be triggered by inspecting, though inspecting does tell you which kind it is.  The best way to handle a chest:<br>
<br>
First, finish your mission, then go back for chests, if it's going to be close.<br>
<br>
1)  Have the rogue/bard target the chest from a distance and sense traps.  If the message they get is &quot;You sense traps,&quot;  &quot;You fail to sense any traps,&quot; or &quot;You're sure the chest is not trapped&quot; then the trap is mechanical... they can keep sensing traps (if they got you fail) until they've found it, then disarm, all without getting close.  Then they can move on to step four.  If they get the message &quot;You can't tell if it's trapped&quot; then it's not mechanical... stand back and move to step two.<br>
<br>
2)  Have a priest cast their curse detection spell on it.  If they get a message &quot;that spell only works on cursed things&quot; go to step 3, otherwise cast the disarm spell and go to step four.<br>
<br>
3)  Have an int caster cast magic trap detection, then cast disarm, then go to step 4.<br>
<br>
4)  Have whoever disarmed the trap move up and try to open the chest with the &quot;open&quot; ability.  If it says it's locked, either pick the lock or or cast a lockpicking spell, then open again.<br>
<br>
5)  Loot, making sure to give all the best loot to the rogue.<br>
